reviewText: It was just as I expected and arrived sooner than I had expected.  It included many hours of entertainment that I had never seen before but would like to keep and watch again.  Gat prompt service.
I really enjoyed these old movies but Scrooge was cut short at the end but love miracle on 34th Street and watched it several times during the holidays.
Just the thing to put me in the Christmas spirit. I didn't even know this version of Miracle on 34th street existed. Loved it.

First off I loved watching the history in these films and they have great acting/story lines.  But when I bought this I thought it was the "Miracle on 34th Street" but it is a 45 min tv version that follows the storyline very closely.  At first it was hard to tell that it wasn't the version I was hoping for.  Honestly great classical cartoons, good selection of older christmas tales that time has forgotten.  It is a great choice but don't be fooled by the titles as they were used multiple times.
